<table id="TBL_Content_10410" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" class="bets border center">
	<tr id="msgbox_10410" class="none">
	<td colspan="7">
		<p class="boxmsg info">
			<span id="ctl00_cphMain_UCOffer_LeagueList_rptLeague_ctl00_ucBettingContainer_lblClose" class="sp icon x1010 xblack" onclick="cbg.DisplayInfo(true,&quot;#msgbox_10410&quot;,false);"></span>
			The UEFA Champions League is the top club competition in European football. It features not only the champions of the best leagues, including the German Bundesliga, the English Premier League, Spain’s La Liga and Serie A in Italy, but also a host of other household names. Real Madrid lead the way, having taken the title twelve times. Milan are the second most successful team in the competition with seven titles. But it’s Real who are the reigning champions once again, becoming the first team in the history of the competition to defend their title. Bayern München, Barcelona and outsiders Liverpool have all won the showpiece event five occasions, and they’re eager to taste glory once more. So, will the Spanish teams dominate again this time around? Bet with top odds on the UEFA Champions League at Interwetten and place Live Bets during the games!
		</p>
	</td>

			Bayern made history last season with their fifth successive league title. And although they failed in their mission to seal a treble – dropping out of both the Champions League and the DFB Cup – they remain the team to beat in the Bundesliga in the 2017/18 season. Moreover, they have strengthened their squad considerably with the addition of James Rodríguez.
RB Leipzig are likely to be hot on their heels again this term, having settled into life in the top flight with ease after their promotion. For much of the last campaign, they kept Bayern on their toes in the push for the title. Dortmund will also be among the chasing pack; however, they have remained rather quiet so far in the transfer market, seemingly happy to rely on the squad that was victorious in the cup. As for the likes of Hoffenheim, Leverkusen, Schalke and Mönchengladbach, it remains to be seen how they will fare, but they are all contenders for one of the top spots.
Interwetten guarantees top odds and a wide variety of betting opportunities for the German Bundesliga, with a Live Betting offer that will keep you on the edge of your seat!

	<td colspan="7">
		<p class="boxmsg info">
			<span id="ctl00_cphMain_UCOffer_LeagueList_rptLeague_ctl10_ucBettingContainer_lblClose" class="sp icon x1010 xblack" onclick="cbg.DisplayInfo(true,&quot;#msgbox_1021&quot;,false);"></span>
			Last season, the Premier League was exciting from start to finish. Ultimately, it was Chelsea who claimed top spot and therefore the 2016/17 title. To defend it, the Blues have already dipped into their transfer kitty. Their biggest arrival is Álvaro Morata from Real Madrid. Chelsea’s rivals for the title - Manchester United, Tottenham, Arsenal and Manchester City – have also made moves in the market, with the Citizens’ purchase of Benjamin Mendy taking the headlines. Costing up to €57.5, he has become the world’s most expensive defender. And City coach Pep Guardiola has made further additions in the hope of landing the league title this time around. As the league with the greatest financial resources, the Premier League really does live up to its name. And we can be sure to see yet another thrilling title race again this season. Interwetten offers top odds and Live Betting on the world’s toughest football league
		</p>

			Juventus have been crowned champions of Serie A every season since the 2011/12 campaign. On top of that, they have done the double three times and reached the Champions League twice in the same period. Therefore, the 'Old Lady' are the clear favourites for the title again this term. But despite their recent dominance, this season could be a different story. Juve's biggest challengers, Roma and Napoli, will be joined by AC Milan, who seem to be ready to battle it out at the top after a few years of falling short. With new signing Leonardo Bonucci from Juventus, they should be well organised at the back. Andre Silva and young star Franck Kessie have also been added to the squad in a bid to topple Juventus. You can follow all of the action in Serie A at Interwetten and bet pre-match and live with the best odds around!

	<td colspan="7">
		<p class="boxmsg info">
			<span id="ctl00_cphMain_UCOffer_LeagueList_rptLeague_ctl20_ucBettingContainer_lblClose" class="sp icon x1010 xblack" onclick="cbg.DisplayInfo(true,&quot;#msgbox_1030&quot;,false);"></span>
			The Spanish Primera Division, also known as La Liga, is contested by 20 clubs. The title race will once again revolve around heavyweights Barcelona and Real Madrid. The record title winning side from the capital are the current champions, finishing top last time around after four straight seasons without league glory. Their French trainer, Zinedine Zidane, now ranks among the most successful in the game, and he’ll be pulling out all the stops to ensure his men defend their title. Germany international Toni Kroos will again be his key man in midfield, pulling the strings and calling the shots. As for the goals, Cristiano Ronaldo, and Barcelona’s Messi and Suarez are likely to be the ones to watch. Atlético Madrid and their superstar Antoine Griezmann are favourites to claim third place behind the big two; however, Sevilla, who have added seven new faces to their squad, Valencia and Athletic Bilbao will all want to have their say. Whatever happens, it’ll probably go down to the wire, so make sure you don’t miss a minute of the action. And with top odds at Interwetten, you’ll can enjoy it all live!
		</p>

	<h4 class="header gradient"><span class="text">Information<label class="sp abs"></label></span></h4>
	<p class="live">Please check the details of your chosen bets very closely on this page. The “Submit betting slip” button is the final step in bet submission. There will be no subsequent confirmation page! Details regarding score and minute of play are purely for purposes of orientation and no responsibility is taken for the correctness of this information.</p>
	<p class="cashout">The Cash-Out function gives you the opportunity to end a bet before the results. This means that you can secure your winnings if the conditions are favourable, as well as minimise your losses if you believe the bet will probably be lost anyway.</p>
	<a class="btn g arrow adv live" onclick="Global.DisplayMessage(&quot;ATTENTION:||Please check the details of your chosen bets very closely on this page. The *Submit betting slip* button is already the final step in bet submission. There will be no subsequent confirm page!||Current scores and ticker times are provided for orientation only and are subject to change and error.||For bets on soccer, ice hockey and handball games, the relevant and valid result of the game is the score at the end of regular playing time. Extra time and penalty shoot-outs have no influence on the bet payment. Exceptions are offered special bets, which are marked accordingly.||For bets on the sports Football, Basketball, and Baseball the result of a possible overtime is decisive for the evaluation of the bet.&quot;);return false;"><span class="large">More information</span><span class="small">Important information about placing your bet</span><label class="icon f08 arrow-right"></label></a>
	<a class="btn g arrow adv cashout" onclick="Global.DisplayMessage(&quot;The Cash-Out feature allows you to have your bet paid out before the respective market closes. This allows you to take a profit if your bet is doing well, or minimise any potential loss should you think the bet is unlikely to result in a win.||Subject to our approval, you can cash out your bet for the amount offered on the Cash-Out tab on your betting slip. If you want to request a Cash-Out of your bet, just select the Cash-Out button.||If your request is successful, your bet will be settled immediately and any funds returned to your account will be equal to the amount shown on the Cash-Out tab on the betting slip. The bet is settled and the final result relating to your initial bet will have no impact on the Cash-Out settlement.||Cash-Out is available for selected betting offers and may be suspended at any time.&quot;);return false;"><span class="large">More information</span><span class="small">Important information on Cash-Out</span><label class="icon f08 arrow-right"></label></a>
